{"title_page": "Year Million", "text_new": "{{short description|TV series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Year Million\n| image = File:National_geographic_year_million.jpg\n| caption = \n| genre = [[Docudrama]]<br>[[Science fiction]]\n| based_on = ''Year Million: Science at the Far Edge of Knowledge'' by [[Damien Broderick]]\n| creator = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Laurence Fishburne]]\n* [[Vinette Robinson]]\n* [[Reece Ritchie]]\n* Joe Corrigall\n* Siobahn Dillon\n* Mikl\u00f3s B\u00e1nyai}}\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Justin Wilkes]]\n* Tommy Turtle\n* Dave O\u2019Connor}}\n| composer = Timo Elliston\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 1\n| num_episodes = 6\n| runtime = 47 minutes\n| company = {{ubl | [[Imagine Entertainment]] | [[RadicalMedia]]}}\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2017|05|15}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| website = http://www.natgeotv.com/int/year-million\n| website_title = Official website\n| production_website = \n| production_website_title = \n| channel = {{ubl | [[National Geographic (U.S. TV channel)|National Geographic]]}}\n}}\n\n'''''Year Million''''' is a six-part documentary and [[science fiction]] television series produced by [[National Geographic (U.S. TV Channel)|National Geographic]], which premiered on May 15, 2017, on their channel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170501005114/en/National-Geographic%E2%80%99s-New-Six-Part-Series-YEAR-MILLIONhttps://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170501005114/en/National-Geographic%E2%80%99s-New-Six-Part-Series-YEAR-MILLION|title=National Geographic\u2019s New Six-Part Series YEAR MILLION Paints a Stunning Picture of Life in the Deep Future|access-date=2018-12-03|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sea.pcmag.com/news/16140/year-million-predicts-a-future-where-humans-are-digital-gods|title='Year Million' Predicts a Future Where Humans Are Digital Gods|date=2017-06-16|work=PCMag Asia|access-date=2018-12-03|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"Inverse.com\">{{cite news |last=Grebey |first=James |title=NatGeo's 'Year Million' Is An Educational Black Mirror |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/31604-year-million-national-geographic-documentary-black-mirror-ai-future |date=May 15, 2017 |work=[[Inverse.com]] |accessdate=May 15, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ars Technica\">{{cite news |last=Newitz |first=Annalee |title=National Geographic series Year Million explores the future of humanity |url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2017/05/get-your-weekly-dose-of-futurism-with-national-geographics-year-million/ |date=May 15, 2017 |work=[[ars Technica]] |accessdate=May 15, 2017}}</ref> The series received two [[Emmy Award]] nominations,<ref name=\"emmys.com\">https://www.emmys.com/shows/year-million</ref><ref name=\"emmyonline.tv\">{{cite web|url=https://emmyonline.tv/2018-news-documentary-emmy-awards/nominees/crafts/|title=Crafts \u2013 The Emmys|website=emmyonline.tv}}</ref>\nincluding a Primetime Emmy for its narrator [[Laurence Fishburne]]. The series is based on the 2008 book ''Year Million: Science at the Far Edge of Knowledge'' by [[Damien Broderick]]. The narrative alternates between the years 2050, 3000, 500,000 and Year Million, using 2016 interviews to explain events unfolding in the story. The series was filmed in Budapest. <ref name=\"Pioneer Films\">{{cite web|url=https://pioneer.hu/films/year-million/|title=Year Million \u2014 Pioneer|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\nInvestigating the ramifications of a variety of potentially world-changing inventions, the series visits a cast of characters representing a typical American family in several different possible timelines through to the year 1,000,000 AD. [[Ray Kurzweil]], [[Michio Kaku]], [[Peter Diamandis]] and [[Brian Greene]] guide the documentary aspect, discussing possible changes the future might hold based on their research: Artificial Intelligence, Man merging with Machine, the human species becoming an interplanetary entity. Exploring life in both the near and the far future, where artificial intelligence is ubiquitous and advances in science have radically extended our lifespans. The series aims to show that communication, work and education will be revolutionized through virtual telepathy.<ref name=\"RadicalMedia.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.radicalmedia.com/work/year-million|title=Year Million - RadicalMedia\u00ae|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nThe series' narrator, [[Laurence Fishburne]], was nominated for a Primetime [[Emmy Award]]<ref name=\"emmys.com\"/>, with a further Craft Emmy Nomination for Outstanding Lighting Direction and Scenic Design <ref name=\"emmyonline.tv\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n\nEach episode of the series is broken up into first narrated scenes, then interviews with scientists and futurologists; the docudrama segments fit around the interviews and narration to illustrate how technological changes might impact a regular family.\n\n[[Laurence Fishburne]] - Narrator<br>Interviews:<br>[[Ray Kurzweil]]<br>[[Michio Kaku]]<br>[[Peter Diamandis]]<br>[[Brian Greene]]<br>Drama:<br>[[Vinette Robinson]] - Eva<br>[[Reece Ritchie]] - Oscar<br>Olive Gray - Jess<br>Joe Corrigall - Damon<br>Siobahn Dillon - Mother<br>Mikl\u00f3s B\u00e1nyai - Newscaster\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| color1     = #FFCC00\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2016)\n| episodes1  = 6\n| start1     = {{Start date|2017|05|15}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2017|06|21}}\n}}\n===Season 1 (2017)===\n{{Episode table |background=#FFCC00 |overall= |season= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Homo Sapien 2.0\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Connolly, Jenny Connell Davis, Jeremy Lubman and Bryan Wizemann\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|05|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = Advances in science and engineering are hastening the day when artificial intelligence may become similar to, or perhaps surpass human intelligence. This episode asks how this might affect our evolution.\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Never Say Die\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Connolly, Jenny Connell Davis, Jeremy Lubman and Bryan Wizemann\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|05|22}}\n  |ShortSummary    = Recent discoveries have given us greater understanding of our biology and how we can live longer... this episode asks if a time may come in our future when our technology transcends beyond treating individual diseases and instead just addresses the aging process itself.\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Dude, Where's My Body?\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Mickey Fisher|t=Mickey Fisher and Paul Solet}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|05|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = Advances in graphics processing and computing generally now mean that we\u2019re seeing the possibilities of working in virtual spaces. This episode asks if there is a potential danger that eventually reality as we know it will be overthrown by the virtual worlds we\u2019ve created for ourselves.\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Mind Meld\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Connolly, Jenny Connell Davis, Jeremy Lubman and Bryan Wizemann\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|06|07}}\n  |ShortSummary    = This episode asks if constant connectivity has affected the privacy that we have always taken for granted. In the deep future, will telepathy be technologically possible, will we even be able to communicate with civilizations beyond Earth?\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Energy Beyond Earth\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = Chris Connolly, Jenny Connell Davis, Jeremy Lubman and Bryan Wizemann\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|06|14}}\n  |ShortSummary    = Overconsumption has led us to a point where the human race will either have to engineer our way around our supply and demand problems, or we will have to look to other planets to inhabit. This episode asks if it is possible that alien civilizations have already solved similar problems.\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Beyond The Cosmos\n |DirectedBy      = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Andr\u00e9 Bormanis|t=Andr\u00e9 Bormanis and Paul Solet}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|06|21}}\n  |ShortSummary    = We have always been a species that is compelled to explore. This spirit has led us to new shores and recently to the planets of our solar system. As the number of places remaining to be explored on Earth vanishes, this episode asks how we might have to adapt ourselves to explore the further reaches of space.\n |LineColor       = #FFCC00\n}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{National Geographic TV}}\n\n[[Category:2017 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2010s American documentary television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about science]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about space]]\n[[Category:Documentary television series about technology]]\n[[Category:National Geographic Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Science education television series]]\n[[Category:Science fiction television films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|TV series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Year Million\n| image = File:National_geographic_year_million.jpg\n| caption = \n| genre = [[Docudrama]]<br>[[Science fiction]]\n| based_on = ''Year Million: Science at the Far Edge of Knowledge'' by [[Damien Broderick]]\n| creator = Mark Elijah Rosenberg\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Laurence Fishburne]]\n* [[Vinette Robinson]]\n* [[Reece Ritchie]]\n* Joe Corrigall\n* Siobahn Dillon\n* Mikl\u00f3s B\u00e1nyai}}\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Justin Wilkes]]\n* Tommy Turtle\n* Dave O\u2019Connor}}\n| composer = Timo Elliston\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 1\n| num_episodes = 6\n| runtime = 47 minutes\n| company = {{ubl | [[Imagine Entertainment]] | [[RadicalMedia]]}}\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2017|05|15}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| website = http://www.natgeotv.com/int/year-million\n| website_title = Official website\n| production_website = \n| production_website_title = \n| channel = {{ubl | [[National Geographic (U.S. TV channel)|National Geographic]]}}\n}}\n\n'''''Year Million''''' is a six-part documentary and [[science fiction]] television series produced by [[National Geographic (U.S. TV Channel)|National Geographic]], which premiered on May 15, 2017, on their channel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170501005114/en/National-Geographic%E2%80%99s-New-Six-Part-Series-YEAR-MILLIONhttps://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170501005114/en/National-Geographic%E2%80%99s-New-Six-Part-Series-YEAR-MILLION|title=National Geographic\u2019s New Six-Part Series YEAR MILLION Paints a Stunning Picture of Life in the Deep Future|access-date=2018-12-03|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sea.pcmag.com/news/16140/year-million-predicts-a-future-where-humans-are-digital-gods|title='Year Million' Predicts a Future Where Humans Are Digital Gods|date=2017-06-16|work=PCMag Asia|access-date=2018-12-03|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"Inverse.com\">{{cite news |last=Grebey |first=James