e and age|1998|04|14}}\n| birth_place = [[North Olmsted, Ohio]], U.S.\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 6\n| weight_lb = 216\n| position = [[Forward (ice hockey)|Forward]]\n| shoots = Left\n| league = [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| team = [[New York Rangers]]\n| prospect_team = [[Hartford Wolf Pack]]\n| prospect_league = [[American Hockey League|AHL]]\n| former_teams = \n| ntl_team = \n| draft = 141st overall\n| draft_year = 2016\n| draft_team = [[New York Rangers]]\n| career_start = 2018\n| career_end =\n}}\n'''Timothy Gettinger''' (born April 14, 1998) is an [[Americans|American]] professional [[ice hockey]] [[Forward (ice hockey)|forward]] for the [[Hartford Wolf Pack]] of the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL) as a prospect to the [[New York Rangers]] of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL). He was selected by the Rangers in the fifth round, 141st overall, in the [[2016 NHL Entry Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Herman |first=Adam |url=https://www.blueshirtbanter.com/2016/6/25/12030198/nhl-draft-2016-rangers-select-left-wing-tim-gettinger-141st-overall |title=NHL Draft 2016: Rangers Select Left Wing Timothy Gettinger 141st Overall |publisher=blueshirtbanter.com |date=June 25, 2016 |accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> He had served as [[Captain (ice hockey)|captain]] for the [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] of the [[Ontario Hockey League]] (OHL).\n\n==Playing career==\nGettinger first played midget hockey in [[Cleveland, Ohio|Cleveland]] with the Barons. In his first season with the [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] of the [[Ontario Hockey League]] (OHL) in the [[2014\u201315 OHL season|2014\u201315 season]], Gettinger scored 10 goals. In the second season with the Greyhounds, his totals improved to 17 goals and 39 points in 60 games for the [[2015\u201316 OHL season|2015\u201316 season]].\n\nOn June 24, 2016, Gettinger was selected 141st overall by the [[New York Rangers]] during the [[2016 NHL Entry Draft]]. Gettinger entered the draft as the 65th ranked prospect.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ben Kerr |url=http://lastwordonsports.com/2016/06/04/tim-gettinger-scouting-report-2016-nhl-draft-65/ |title=Tim Gettinger Scouting Report: 2016 NHL Draft #65 |publisher=lastwordonsports.com |date=June 4, 2016| accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn March 16, 2017, the Rangers signed Gettinger to a three-year, entry-level contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rangers Agree to Terms With Forward Tim Gettinger |url=https://www.nhl.com/rangers/news/rangers-agree-to-terms-with-forward-tim-gettinger/c-287765306 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=November 26, 2018 |date=March 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn October 12, 2017, Gettinger was named [[Captain (ice hockey)|captain]] of the Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ruicci |first1=Peter |title=Greyhounds name Gettinger captain |url=http://www.saultstar.com/2017/10/12/greyhounds-name-gettinger-captain |website=Sault Star |accessdate=October 25, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026110719/http://www.saultstar.com/2017/10/12/greyhounds-name-gettinger-captain |archivedate=October 26, 2017 |date=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\nGettinger began the 2018\u201319 season with the [[Hartford Wolf Pack]] of the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL). He was recalled by the Rangers due to an injury to forward [[Mats Zuccarello]] on November 23, 2018, and played his first NHL game the next day with the Rangers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rangers Recall Tim Gettinger From Hartford |url=https://www.nhl.com/rangers/news/rangers-recall-tim-gettinger-from-hartford/c-302228142 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=November 26, 2018 |date=November 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Brooks |first1=Larry |title=Rangers playing it \u2018cautious\u2019 with Mats Zuccarello |url=https://nypost.com/2018/11/24/rangers-playing-it-cautious-with-mats-zuccarello/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=November 26, 2018 |date=November 24, 2018}}</ref> He was returned to Harford after playing one game,<ref>{{cite web |title=Rangers' Tim Gettinger sent back down to Hartford after Saturday's game |url=https://www.sny.tv/rangers/news/rangers-tim-gettinger-sent-back-down-to-hartford-after-saturdays-game/301069904 |website=SNY |accessdate=November 25, 2018 |date=November 24, 2018}}</ref> only to be recalled the next day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rangers Recall Tim Gettinger From Hartford |url=https://www.nhl.com/rangers/news/rangers-recall-tim-gettinger-from-hartford/c-302295932 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=November 29, 2018 |date=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career Statistics==\n===Regular season and playoffs===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Regular season]] \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Playoffs]] \n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! GP\n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]]\n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]]\n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]]\n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]]\n! GP\n! G\n! A\n! Pts\n! PIM\n|-\n| [[2014\u201315 OHL season|2014\u201315]]\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]]\n| [[Ontario Hockey League|OHL]]\n| 54\n| 10\n| 15\n| 25\n| 13\n| 6\n| 1\n| 1\n| 2\n| 2\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[2015\u201316 OHL season|2015\u201316]]\n| Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds\n| OHL\n| 60\n| 17\n| 22\n| 39\n| 32\n| 12\n| 1\n| 3\n| 4\n| 0\n|- \n| [[2016\u201317 OHL season|2016\u201317]]\n| Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds\n| OHL\n| 62\n| 31\n| 23\n| 54\n| 27\n| 11\n| 4\n| 3\n| 7\n| 0\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[2017\u201318 OHL season|2017\u201318]]\n| Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds\n| OHL\n| 63\n| 33\n| 36\n| 69\n| 53\n| 24\n| 7\n| 15\n| 22\n| 4\n|- \n| [[2018\u201319 AHL season|2018\u201319]]\n| [[Hartford Wolf Pack]]\n| [[American Hockey League|AHL]]\n| 64\n| 14\n| 13\n| 27\n| 27\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| [[2018\u201319 NHL season|2018\u201319]]\